en_765312_0	Sixty five children have been hospitalized following food poisoning.
en_765312_1	Twenty of them are still in hospital receiving treatment.
en_765312_2	The Police and Public Health Inspectors have begun investigations into the incident.
en_765312_3	A religious institute non-governmental organization had distributed food among 160 children from the Templestowe Estates in Watawala Police division.
en_765312_4	It had caused an allergic reaction.
en_765312_5	Thereafter sixty five children were admitted to the Watawala Base Hospital.
en_765312_6	Several children in a critical condition were transferred to the Nawalapitiya Hospital.
en_765312_7	17 children are still receiving treatment at the Watawala Hospital while three of them are further receiving treatment at the Nawalapitiya Hospital.
en_765312_8	The relevant religious institution conducts after school classes and provides lunch, for the children in the estate daily.
